Russia, Ukraine agree on ‘humanitarian corridors’ to let people trapped in besieged cities leave
Russian troops seized a key government building in Kherson and more than 1 million refugees have left Ukraine, as Russia’s invasion begins a second week. (Jason Aldag/The Washington Post)
By David L. Stern
